HEADWORD: Cats-eye
<hw>Cat's"-eye`</hw> <pr>(k⟦acr⟧ts"⟦imac⟧`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A variety of quartz or chalcedony, exhibiting
opalescent reflections from within, like the eye of a cat. The name is
given to other gems affording like effects, esp. the
chrysoberyl.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

